en_225436_0	The Meteorology Department forecasts thundershowers in the sea areas off the coast extending from Mannar to Colombo and Galle via Matara during the next 24 hours.
en_225436_1	The Department stated that temporary strong winds could be experienced in the region of 70 to 80 kilometers per hour during thundershowers.
en_225436_2	Meanwhile, the Western, Sabaragamuwa, Central, North Western and Uva provinces, as well as the districts of Galle, Matara and Anuradhapura could experience rainfall of more than 75 mm after 2 pm.
en_225436_3	The Department has advised the public to be vigilant of lightning accidents that could occur during thundershowers.
